  "description": "Fully symmetric fold (symmetry 1.0) at high fold amount — perfect symmetry suppresses odd harmonics, producing a bright even-harmonic spectrum similar to a ring-modulated signal. The pitch is shifted up a fifth (7 semitones) to use the harmonic material in a higher register. A pleated spectrum: every fold doubles back on the last.",
